In reaction to xenophobic attacks to Nigerians in South African Afro Fusion star and ‘African Giant’, Burna Boy has declared he would never set foot in the country until government of South Africa addresses the problem. The multi-award winning star says this in a series of posts. Xenophobic attack: Direct Nigerians to return home, CSOs tells FG(Opens in a new browser tab) See his statement below:   – Burna Boy speaks out on the issue at hand with xenophobia. A post shared by  Tunde Ednut (@tundeednut) on Sep 3, 2019 at 12:08pm PDT  Vanguard Damini Ogulu, a.k.a Burna Boy, Nigerian Afro-fusion singer and songwriter, has hit the market with another party starter called ‘Anybody’. June 14, 2019 In "News" Angry Nigerians, yesterday, stormed the South African High Commission in Abuja, threatening to shut down South African companies in Nigeria over xenophobic attacks against foreigners in South Africa, including Nigerians. April 21, 2015 In "Headlines" On Wednesday night, DJ Jimmy Jatt, Ice Prince, Skiibi, Larry Gaga, Sensei Uche, Dammy Krane, Dremo, Peruzzi, among many other entertainers, joined Afro-fusion music singer, Burna Boy at Club Quilox, to celebrate his big win at the just-concluded BET awards. July 5, 2019 In "Entertainment"